item.title: Mary Nohl's art and love of tools at the Kohler Arts Center
item.description:
Mary Nohl's art and love of tools at the Kohler Arts Center

Sheboygan -- Much written about in these pages and much revered in our region, the late Mary Nohl has become an artist of great renown. The fate of her home on Lake Michigan in Fox Point, one of the only intact, artist-made environments created by a woman in the world, has long been a source of debate between art lovers and local residents.
